Modern computer networks require sophisticated protocol integration for reliable communication. Current implementations often operate in isolation, limiting effectiveness in real-world scenarios. This research develops a simulation frame-work combining Routing Information Protocol (RIP), Prim's algorithm, TCP Tahoe congestion control, and CRC-16-CCITT error detection. The goal is to design an integrated protocol stack coordinating routing, transport, and error detection lay-ers. The work evaluates performance under realistic conditions and demonstrates cross-layer optimization effectiveness. The framework provides end-to-end communication with dynamic routing and robust error detection. Experimental evaluation using “Computer Network Protocol PBL” data shows 94.7% packet delivery success rate, validating the framework's real-world potential.